<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-10-15T17:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-07-28T18:00:00-05:00" n="246" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d246">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">C.P.(Gen)Doc.1.T.1.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="smallcaps">Article 64</hi></head>
                        <dateline>
                            <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-outside-research" calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1946-10-15T23:59:59+01:00" notBefore="1946-07-29T00:00:00+01:00">undated</date>
                        </dateline>
                        <p>Addition to Article 64 of the Peace treaty with Italy: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“The basis for calculation for the payment of indemnity will be
                                    the United States dollar, at its gold parity on the day of the
                                    signing of the Peace treaty, i.e. 35 dollars for one ounce of
                                    gold.”</p>
                            </quote></p>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>